that I'd understand ♪

36:06.114 --> 36:08.899
♪ how it feels
to love a girl ♪

36:08.950 --> 36:12.869
♪ I swear
I'd be a better man ♪

36:15.990 --> 36:20.860
♪ I'd listen to her

36:20.878 --> 36:24.080
♪ 'cause I know
how it hurts ♪

36:27.635 --> 36:30.203
♪ when you lose
the one you wanted ♪

36:30.221 --> 36:33.056
♪ 'cause he's
taking you for granted ♪

36:33.090 --> 36:38.678
♪ and everything you had
got destroyed ♪

36:38.712 --> 36:42.682
♪ but you're just a boy

36:45.403 --> 36:49.606
[cheers and applause]

36:51.242 --> 36:52.659
Yeah.

36:54.512 --> 36:57.831
Tom, what's the matter?
What's wrong?

36:57.865 --> 37:01.117
I can't put that number
in Bombshell.

37:01.169 --> 37:05.105
- Oh.
- I'm sorry.

37:05.139 --> 37:06.690
Hmm.
I knew it.

37:06.724 --> 37:09.125
You'd be amazing in it,
and I'd love to see you

37:09.160 --> 37:11.778
do it someday,
but Julia's right.

37:11.796 --> 37:13.814
The Kennedy number
is better for the show.

37:13.848 --> 37:16.650
You know, I left my job
for this.

37:16.684 --> 37:19.336
You left your job
because you're unhappy.

37:19.370 --> 37:22.589
I left my job
for a lot of reasons.

37:22.607 --> 37:23.940
And I thought you'd changed.

37:23.975 --> 37:25.692
I thought you were
finally ready for this,

37:25.726 --> 37:26.943
but you're
the same old Tom,

37:26.994 --> 37:28.345
putting work before
what's really important.

37:28.379 --> 37:29.496
Where are you going?

37:29.530 --> 37:31.982
To see if I can get
my job back.

37:34.769 --> 37:36.820
Oh, hey.
I had another idea...

37:36.854 --> 37:40.290
A way to differentiate
between my Marilyn and Karen's.

37:40.324 --> 37:42.275
I thought maybe we could redo
a couple of the costumes.

37:42.293 --> 37:43.660
Yeah, I don't think so.

37:43.711 --> 37:44.911
I was only thinking
maybe one or two.

37:44.929 --> 37:46.930
They're perfect
the way they are.

37:46.964 --> 37:48.265
We're also not going
to be able to work in

37:48.299 --> 37:49.599
that break for you
in act two.

37:49.634 --> 37:50.817
I'm sorry.

37:50.852 --> 37:52.536
Can we at least
discuss it?

37:52.570 --> 37:54.120
We just did.

37:54.154 --> 37:56.673
Mm, but your note
about the catch breath,

37:56.707 --> 37:57.741
that was spot-on.

37:57.775 --> 37:58.992
Great job.

37:59.026 --> 38:01.094
Places, everyone,
for the top.

38:01.128 --> 38:05.715
Let's run the whole shebang,
no stopping.

38:05.766 --> 38:07.684
How'd it go?

38:07.718 --> 38:09.486
I cut it.

38:09.520 --> 38:11.821
I know that was hard.

38:11.873 --> 38:13.256
Yes, it was.

38:13.307 --> 38:15.342
But it was also right.

38:15.376 --> 38:16.860
Mm hmm.

38:16.894 --> 38:19.779
I need you to take another
pass on the Gladys scenes.

38:19.814 --> 38:20.947
- What?
- I know how much

38:20.982 --> 38:22.749
they mean to you,

38:22.767 --> 38:24.067
but I need them to be
a little more focused.

38:24.101 --> 38:25.051
Take out the fat.

38:25.069 --> 38:27.153
- Okay.
- By tonight.

38:27.188 --> 38:29.122
Apparently, Eileen has
a name lined up.

38:29.156 --> 38:31.508
She's on her way here now.

38:31.542 --> 38:33.460
I'll go start on it now.

38:33.494 --> 38:37.731
Good.

38:37.765 --> 38:39.566
Relax for two minutes.

38:39.600 --> 38:42.068
- I have some news.
- Lupone?

38:42.086 --> 38:43.720
No, I want to go
in a new direction.

38:43.754 --> 38:46.323
Leigh Conroy has agreed
to come out of retirement

38:46.357 --> 38:48.909
and play the part of Gladys.

38:48.943 --> 38:52.262
- Ivy's mother.
- It's a good story, Tom.

38:52.296 --> 38:54.564
The New York Times has agreed
to announce it

38:54.615 --> 38:56.399
as soon as we pull
the trigger.

38:56.450 --> 38:59.369
That is, of course,
unless you think

38:59.403 --> 39:02.472
Ivy might feel threatened.

39:02.523 --> 39:06.676
[Indistinct chatter]

39:06.711 --> 39:07.894
Do it.

39:07.912 --> 39:10.830
- I'll make the call.
- All right.

39:10.864 --> 39:12.315
Bobby, stop texting.
Places for real.

39:12.350 --> 39:14.467
Everyone full out.
Don't let me see the mistakes.

39:14.501 --> 39:18.788
I just paid 134.50 twice
and a babysitter.

39:18.823 --> 39:20.773
Congratulations.

39:20.791 --> 39:22.459
[Alternative rock music
playing]

39:22.493 --> 39:24.210
You just became our diva.

39:24.244 --> 39:25.879
[Laughs]
What? Hey.

39:25.913 --> 39:27.480
I'm sorry
I didn't see it before.

39:27.514 --> 39:29.866
I'll accept
if you buy me another drink.

39:29.900 --> 39:30.900
Sure thing.

39:30.918 --> 39:33.753
[Laughs]

39:33.788 --> 39:36.756
So let me ask you
a serious question.

39:38.926 --> 39:41.978
Should we have
one more drink?

39:42.029 --> 39:43.530
Yeah, I think you've had
enough tonight.

39:43.564 --> 39:45.498
Come on.

39:45.533 --> 39:46.850
This is the first time
we've been out in ages,

39:46.884 --> 39:48.852
and you've been
blowing me off lately.

39:48.886 --> 39:51.004
Yeah, I know.

39:51.038 --> 39:53.206
Why?

39:53.240 --> 39:55.241
Do you like me or not?

39:55.276 --> 39:57.610
- Of course I like you.
- No.

39:57.644 --> 40:00.230
I mean, do you like me?

40:00.264 --> 40:02.882
♪

40:02.917 --> 40:06.853
Either of you guys
want a drink?

40:06.887 --> 40:07.988
Walk me home.

40:08.022 --> 40:11.791
Yeah, my pleasure.

40:11.826 --> 40:13.843
Oh, hey,
is Ana going with you?

40:13.894 --> 40:17.147
Uh, no, I think
she's taken care of.

40:17.181 --> 40:19.065
As is Kyle.

40:19.099 --> 40:23.253
See you
at rehearsals tomorrow.

40:23.304 --> 40:26.322
Yeah, night.

40:26.357 --> 40:29.842
Thanks for walking me home.

40:29.860 --> 40:31.861
I can take it from here.

40:31.896 --> 40:34.981
You sure?

40:34.999 --> 40:36.900
Don't need
an escort upstairs?

40:36.934 --> 40:38.802
[Laughs]

40:38.853 --> 40:39.934
We could get another drink.

40:39.937 --> 40:43.606
I know a spot
on the corner.

40:43.657 --> 40:46.376
I have an early rehearsal
tomorrow,

40:46.410 --> 40:50.480
and the director
is a control freak.

40:50.514 --> 40:52.365
[Tender music]

40:52.400 --> 40:56.619
Fair enough.

40:56.654 --> 40:58.154
Good night.

40:58.205 --> 40:59.989
Night.

41:00.041 --> 41:06.262
